Description.Text: Hotel is very modern in style with a great location and offers and very high quality product. MW 1106

The hotel has a very central location. It is 2 minutes walk from Red Square and one street away from the Bolshoi Theatre. The Kremlin and St Basil's Cathedral are situated a short walk away. The hotel has good public transport connections nearby.

Rooms are medium sized and tastefully decorated in a mix of warm colours. They are extremely well appointed and have the excellent facilities expected of a niche property such as this. The bathrooms are decorated using marble tiles with separate shower and are very generous in size.
Hotel is a modern building supported by a base of marble and huge pillars situated in the heart of the city.

The main restaurant is located on the 1st floor and is modern in design. The walls are covered with bright and colourful paintings by local artists. There is an Armenian restaurant on the ground floor together with a small sushi bar.

Hotel has large atrium style lobby with adequate seating area. The floor is decorated with black marble tiles but the light walls and large glass lifts give a spacious feel to it. The lobby leads down to a cosy bar area which provides further seating capacity.
